  "response": "Instagram has significantly limited the ability to see the likes of other users. Here's a breakdown of what you can and cannot do:\n\n**What you CAN'T Do:**\n\n*   **See a comprehensive list of everyone someone has liked.** Instagram removed the \"Following\" tab, which used to allow you to see the recent activity of people you follow, including their likes. This feature no longer exists.\n*   **Use third-party apps to reliably see someone's likes.** Many apps that claim to do this are scams or violate Instagram's terms of service. They might ask for your login credentials and compromise your account.\n\n**What you CAN Do:**\n\n*   **See likes on your own posts:** You can see who has liked your own posts.\n*   **See likes on posts you both follow:** If you and the person you're interested in both follow the same account, you can see if they liked a post from that account.\n*   **Manually browse their following's posts.** This is very time-consuming but could potentially give you a glimpse.\n*   **If their account is public, you can see the number of likes on their posts.** However, this only tells you *how many* people liked it, not *who* specifically.\n\n**Why the Changes?**\n\nInstagram removed the \"Following\" tab and restricted like-viewing for privacy reasons. They cited concerns about stalking and unwanted attention.\n\n**In short, there's no reliable and legitimate way to see a comprehensive list of someone's likes on Instagram.** Be wary of any apps or services that promise otherwise.",
